[7915070]

The current jump times are 11:00 and 23:00 CET. I get the logic for them in terms of convenience, but with reference to the cycle changes and gold days, they don't make sense, since they fall into cycles 4 and 8 (or 5 and 1 on other ships). The objective should be to get in as early during the game day as possible, so anything with a chance of jumping into cycle 8 is out of the question. Of course lots of people can't stay up late enough to get in at cycle 1/2, but probably starting the other jump at cycle 3/4 would be okay for many of those, no need to wait for the next one IMO.

The cycle changes for cycle 1 and cycle 3 (or 2 and 4 on other ships) are at 1:00 and 7:00 CET. I would suggest making those the two Sunday jumps, since they're optimal for gold players. They're not the nicest possible times to jump at, but you only need to do it once per game. I guess the later one could be moved back by an hour or two, as long as it still falls into cycle 3/4 rather than 4/5. We can hope that eventually the devs will make the gold system smarter, but for now we have to work within its limits.
